            // Page 1 - Overview and Basic Features
            `
                <h4>Chart of Account - Overview</h4>
                <p>This page allows you to manage your chart of accounts in the accounting system.</p>

                <h5>Main Features:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Create New Account:</strong> Click the "NEW" button to add a new account to the system</li>
                    <li><strong>View Accounts:</strong> Browse through the hierarchical account tree structure</li>
                    <li><strong>Edit Accounts:</strong> Select any account from the tree to modify its details</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete Accounts:</strong> Remove unused or obsolete accounts from the system</li>
                    <li><strong>Search Accounts:</strong> Use the search function to quickly locate specific accounts</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Account Tree Structure:</h5>
                <p>Accounts are organized in a hierarchical tree format, allowing you to create parent-child relationships for better organization and reporting.</p>
            `,

            // Page 2 - Creating and Managing Accounts
            `
                <h4>Creating and Managing Accounts</h4>

                <h5>How to Create a New Account:</h5>
                <ol>
                    <li>Select a parent node from the account tree (this is required)</li>
                    <li>Click the "+ NEW" button in the top right corner</li>
                    <li>Fill in the account details in the form</li>
                    <li>Assign a unique account code</li>
                    <li>Save the account to add it to the system</li>
                </ol>

                <h5>Editing Existing Accounts:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li>Click on any account in the tree to view its details</li>
                    <li>Modify the necessary fields in the form</li>
                    <li>Save your changes to update the account</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Account Codes:</h5>
                <p>Each account must have a unique code. Use a systematic numbering scheme that makes sense for your organization (e.g., 1000-1999 for Assets, 2000-2999 for Liabilities).</p>
            `,

            // Page 3 - Important Rules and Restrictions
            `
                <h4>Important Notes and Restrictions</h4>

                <h5>Critical Requirements:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Tree Node Selection:</strong> You must select a parent tree node before creating a new account. The "NEW" button will be disabled until a node is selected.</li>
                    <li><strong>Unique Account Codes:</strong> Account codes must be unique within the entire system. Duplicate codes will be rejected.</li>
                    <li><strong>Parent Account Deletion:</strong> Parent accounts that have child accounts cannot be deleted. You must first delete or move all child accounts.</li>
                    <li><strong>Active Accounts:</strong> Accounts with existing transactions cannot be deleted. They must be marked as inactive instead.</li>
                </ul>

                <h5>Data Validation:</h5>
                <p>The system will validate your input to ensure data integrity. Make sure all required fields are filled correctly before saving.</p>
